    "content_hash": "03999ea95a23358d",
    "department": "Data Analytics and AI",
    "description": "At Snowflake, we are powering the era of the agentic enterprise. To usher in this new era, we seek AI-native thinkers across every function who are energized by the opportunity to reinvent how they work. You don’t just use tools; you possess an innate curiosity, treating AI as a high-trust collaborator that is core to how you solve problems and accelerate your impact. We look for low-ego individuals who thrive in dynamic and fast-moving environments and move with an experimental mindset — who rapidly test emerging capabilities to discover simpler, more powerful ways to deliver results. At Snowflake, your role isn't just to execute a function, but to help redefine the future of how work gets done.\n\nSnowflake is seeking a senior, business-facing leader to serve as Sr. Manager, People Analytics. This role is responsible for building and operating a modern people analytics function that directly informs executive decisions, workforce strategy, and operating cadence across the company.\n\nReporting to the Director, Data Analytics \u0026 AI, this leader will move people analytics beyond descriptive reporting into a trusted input for leadership decisions and employee enablement. The function will integrate people data with financial and product signals and power AI-driven experiences that help leaders and employees make better decisions, faster.\n\nThis role sits at the intersection of workforce strategy, enterprise analytics, and AI enablement. The Sr. Manager will partner closely with HR, Finance, Product, and senior leaders to ensure people data is governed, explainable, and actionable, and that it meaningfully shapes how Snowflake plans, invests, scales, and works.\n\n\nKEY RESPONSIBILITIES:\n\n\nPeople Analytics Strategy and Leadership\n\n - Define and own Snowflake’s people analytics strategy as a core enterprise capability aligned to company priorities and executive decision-making needs.\n\n - Position people analytics as a trusted input into workforce planning, operating model design, and investment decisions.\n\n - Partner with the CDAO, CHRO, CFO, Product leadership, and executive team on the people questions that matter most to the business.\n   \n\nAI-Powered Employee Enablement\n\n - Lead the development of AI-driven people analytics experiences, including AI agents that help leaders and employees access insights, answer questions, and take action using governed people data.\n\n - Translate workforce and HR use cases into scalable, production-grade AI agents embedded in employee workflows.\n\n - Ensure AI agents are built with strong guardrails around privacy, security, explainability, and responsible use.\n   \n\nBusiness Impact and Decision Enablement\n\n - Connect people data and AI-driven insights to business outcomes, including productivity, execution velocity, attrition risk, talent gaps, and cost efficiency.\n\n - Build decision frameworks that help leaders move from insight to action, particularly during periods of growth, re-orgs, and transformation.\n\n - Establish clear metrics, narratives, and guardrails that support confident, timely, and accountable decision-making.\n   \n\nAnalytics, AI, and Platform Integration\n\n - Partner closely with Data and and Analytics engineering teams to deliver reporting, predictive insights, and AI powered applications.\n\n - Leverage Snowflake’s data and AI platform to partner with the Analytics Engineering team to build scalable, certified people datasets and AI agents integrated with enterprise analytics.\n\n - Partner with data science and AI teams to apply advanced analytics and AI responsibly, with an emphasis on transparency and trust.\n   \n\nGovernance and Data Integrity\n\n - Set strong governance, privacy, and security standards for sensitive people data.\n\n - Ensure people analytics and AI outputs are consistent, explainable, and aligned with enterprise\n\n - Act as a steward of trust for employees and leaders in how people data and AI tools are used.\n   \n\nTeam Leadership and Operating Excellence\n\n - Build, lead, and scale a high-performing people analytics team with expertise across analytics, business partnership, and AI product delivery.\n\n - Provide clear direction, coaching, and career development for managers and individual contributors.\n\n - Establish scalable operating processes that prioritize high-leverage work and measurable impact.\n\nDrive adoption of people's insights and AI tools through strong storytelling, data fluency, and partnership.\n\n\nQUALIFICATIONS:\n\n\n - Bachelor’s degree in a quantitative or analytical field; advanced degree preferred.\n\n - 8+ years of experience in people analytics, enterprise analytics, data science, or strategy roles with increasing scope and complexity.\n\n - Demonstrated people management experience, including hiring, developing, and leading high-performing teams in matrixed or high-growth environments.\n\n - Experience building or partnering on AI-powered analytics products or agents in enterprise settings.\n\n - Proven ability to influence senior leaders and operate effectively in complex organizations.\n\n - Strong systems thinker with executive presence and comfort operating in ambiguity.\n\n - Deep analytics expertise, strong SQL skills, and experience integrating HR data into enterprise data platforms.\n\n - Familiarity with governed AI development, including privacy, explainability, and security considerations.\n\nEvery Snowflake employee is expected to follow the company’s confidentiality and security standards for handling sensitive data. Snowflake employees must abide by the company’s data security plan as an essential part of their duties. It is every employee's duty to keep customer information secure and confidential.\n\nSnowflake is growing fast, and we’re scaling our team to help enable and accelerate our growth. We are looking for people who share our values, challenge ordinary thinking, and push the pace of innovation while building a future for themselves and Snowflake.\n\nHow do you want to make your impact?\n\nFor jobs located in the United States, please visit the job posting on the Snowflake Careers Site for salary and benefits information: careers.snowflake.com http://careers.snowflake.com",
